# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets headers for icons.tsuchiyalab.com.
#
# Image-noindex policy (TSUCHIYA LAB): HTML stays indexable, images
# do not. Primary defense is robots.txt User-agent: Googlebot-Image
# Disallow; this file adds X-Robots-Tag: noindex, noimageindex as a
# secondary signal. The `noimageindex` directive specifically tells
# Google Images not to use the asset.
#
# Aligned with RUN-TSUCHIYALAB-ALL-SITES-IMAGE-NOINDEX-POLICY-01.
#
# Workers Static Assets requires a leading slash on the match URL
# (Pages accepts bare `*.png`, but the Workers validator rejects it).
# `/*.png` matches any path that ends with `.png`.

/*.png
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, noimageindex

/*.jpg
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, noimageindex

/*.jpeg
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, noimageindex

/*.webp
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, noimageindex

/*.gif
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, noimageindex

/*.avif
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, noimageindex

/*.ico
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, noimageindex

# .svg is intentionally not blanket-blocked — the TSUCHIYA LAB mark
# (tsuchiyalab-mark.svg) is a brand asset that should remain indexable.
